# Inside .xcodeproj: keep project.pbxproj and xcshareddata, drop user state.
*.xcodeproj/xcuserdata/
*.xcodeproj/project.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/
*.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/

# Don't commit Xcode shared schemes — Xcode's "Edit Scheme..." dialog
# saves environment variables (including credentials like
# OPENSKY_CLIENT_SECRET) into the SHARED scheme by default. We've had
# this leak TWICE. Schemes still work fine without being shared —
# Xcode auto-creates a user-scheme on first open.
#
# Previous patterns missed the leading **/ and were root-anchored —
# gitignore semantics treat a mid-path slash as anchored to the
# .gitignore's directory, not "match anywhere". The actual scheme
# path is nested under ios/Tailspot/, so the rule never fired.
# Belt-and-suspenders: also gitignore *.xcscheme by filename.
**/*.xcodeproj/xcshareddata/xcschemes/
**/*.xcworkspace/xcshareddata/xcschemes/
*.xcscheme

